  "title": "Marketing and PR Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Location:</strong> Primarily work from home; one in-person meeting per week</p><h2>Working Hours & Schedule</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Total Hours:</strong> 30 hours per week</p></li><li><p><strong>Workdays:</strong> Monday to Friday</p></li><li><p><strong>Daily Hours:</strong> 6 hours per day</p></li><li><p><strong>Core Availability:</strong> Any continuous 6-hour window between <strong>11:00 AM - 8:00 PM (weekdays)</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Daily schedule can be determined based on the successful applicant’s availability</p></li></ul><h3>Weekly In-Person Meeting</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Frequency:</strong> Once per week</p></li><li><p><strong>Duration:</strong> Up to 2 hours</p></li><li><p><strong>Note:</strong> This meeting counts toward the total weekly working hours</p></li></ul><h2>Leave Entitlement</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Medical Leave:</strong> 7 days per year</p></li><li><p><strong>Annual Leave:</strong> 14 days per year</p></li></ul><h2>Scope of Work</h2><h3>Personal Support</h3><ul><li><p>Create and manage content for LinkedIn profile</p></li><li><p>Plan, coordinate, and organize monthly meetings to strengthen professional and social relationships</p></li><li><p>Track and remind of birthdays and important personal or professional events</p></li><li><p>Organize and manage budgeting for gift purchases</p></li></ul><h3>Singa Credit Pte Ltd</h3><ul><li><p>Create and manage content for <strong>LinkedIn, Facebook, and Instagram</strong> (content will be repurposed across platforms)</p></li><li><p>Create and monitor content performance for the website</p></li><li><p>Produce videos for <strong>Singa TV</strong> for every public holiday</p></li></ul><h3>Landscaping Company</h3><ul><li><p>Create and manage content on <strong>Carousell</strong></p></li><li><p>Create content for the <strong>website, Facebook, and Instagram</strong></p></li></ul><h2>Compensation</h2><ul><li><p>Base pay to be discussed with shortlisted candidates</p></li><li><p><strong>Additional Pay:</strong> Seasonal work may be compensated with additional pay, capped at <strong>$300</strong>. Feasibility and structure to be discussed during the interview process.</p></li></ul><h2>Ideal Candidate</h2><ul><li><p>Strong content creation and organizational skills</p></li><li><p>Comfortable managing multiple brands and platforms</p></li><li><p>Proactive, detail-oriented, and able to work independently</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with social media platforms and basic content performance tracking</p></li></ul>",
